 emerges is a compelling picture of how the Garifuna engage ancestral spirits across multiple diasporic horizons. His study sheds new light on the ways diasporic religions around the world creatively plot itineraries of spatial memory that at once recover and remold their histories.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 24. Apr 2020) 0aGarifuna (Caribbean people)xEthnic identityxHonduras. 0aGarifuna (Caribbean people)xEthnic identityxNew York (State)xNew York Metropolitan Area. 0aGarifuna (Caribbean people)xEthnic identity. 0aGarifuna (Caribbean people)xMigrationsxHonduras. 0aGarifuna (Caribbean people)xReligionxHonduras. 0aGarifuna (Caribbean people)xReligionxNew York (State)xNew York Metropolitan Area. 0aGarifuna (Caribbean people)xReligion. 0aGarifuna (Caribbean people)zHondurasxEthnic identity. 0aGarifuna (Caribbean people)zHondurasxMigrations. 0aGarifuna (Caribbean people)zHondurasxReligion. 0aGarifuna (Caribbean people)zNew York (State)zNew York Metropolitan AreaxEthnic identity. 0aGarifuna (Caribbean people)zNew York (State)zNew York Metropolitan AreaxReligion. 7aRELIGION / Comparative Religion.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUC Press eBook Package 2000-2015z978311066334108iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUC Press eBook Package Backlist 2000-2013z978311069042240uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780520940215423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9780520940215.jpg  a978-3-11-066334-1  UC Press eBook Package 2000-2015c2000d2015  a978-3-11-069042-2  UC Press eBook Package Backlist 2000-2013c2000d2013  aEBA_FAO  aGBV-deGruyter-alles